  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Display SpriteKit content on the screen by configuring a SpriteKit renderer, its scene, and the visual objects you lay out on top of the scene. SpriteKit provides objects that are designed specifically for various types of content (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/nodes_for_scene_building"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "), but for simplicity, this article displays an image in a view. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "There are other ways to draw SpriteKit content besides using a view. See "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/choosing_a_spritekit_scene_renderer"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " for options. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3016873",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3016873",
                "title": "Figure 1",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "An image displayed in a SpriteKit view"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Because the code in this article sets up a view, you put the lines from each of the following code listings into a view controller's "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontroller/1621495-viewdidload"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Create the Scene",
          "anchor": "3016859"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Everything displayed with SpriteKit is done through a scene object, which is an instance of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Use the following code to set up a basic scene: "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let scene = SKScene(size: skView.bounds.size)",
            "",
            "// Set the scene coordinates (0, 0) to the center of the screen.",
            "scene.anchorPoint = CGPoint(x: 0.5, y: 0.5)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3016857",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you pass the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "size"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " of the view's "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "bounds"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to the scene initializer, you size the scene to the view's size. When you set the scene's "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscene/1519864-anchorpoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(0.5, 0.5)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", you determine that the coordinates (0, 0) map to the center of the view.   "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For further discussion about how setting the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "anchorPoint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " changes an object's position in the view, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Using the Anchor Point to Move the Spriteâ€™s Frame",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/GraphicsAnimation/Conceptual/SpriteKit_PG/Sprites/Sprites.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40013043-CH9-SW36"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Lay Out Visual Content on Top of the Scene",
          "anchor": "3016851"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You use node objects to display graphics in a SpriteKit view. SpriteKit provides different nodes depending on the content (see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/nodes_for_scene_building#2242745"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "). In this case, use an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skspritenode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to display an image in the view: "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let image = SKSpriteNode(imageNamed: \"myImage.png\")",
            "",
            "// Add the image to the scene.",
            "scene.addChild(image)",
            ""
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3016853",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The functions to lay out content in a scene are covered in more detail in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/accessing_and_modifying_the_node_tree"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Present the Scene Inside a View",
          "anchor": "3016862"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "After you set up the scene, you display it in the view by calling "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skview/1519705-presentscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ": "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "if let skView = self.view as? SKView { ",
            "    skView.presentScene(scene)",
            "}",
            ""
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3016855",
            "title": "Listing 3"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Because the code in this article sets up a view, you add it to your view controller's "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontroller/1621495-viewdidload"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
